1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of Dr. James
2 Votruba.
3 WHEREAS, Dr. James Votruba was a visionary and compassionate leader, mentor,
4 and steward of northern Kentucky; and
5 WHEREAS, Dr. James Votruba was the fourth and longest-serving president of
6 Northern Kentucky University, serving from 1997 to 2012. During his tenure, he
7 shepherded the growth of the university through enrollment increases, the addition of
8 colleges and post-baccalaureate programs, major construction projects, and preparations
9 for reclassification as a National Collegiate Athletic Association Division I institution for
10 athletics; and
11 WHEREAS, Dr. James Votruba firmly believed in and fostered the role of Northern
12 Kentucky University as a student-centered institution focused on advancing regional
13 economic, social, and civic progress in the northern Kentucky and greater Cincinnati
14 communities; and
15 WHEREAS, beyond his work with Northern Kentucky University, Dr. James
16 Votruba spent time on boards and groups to improve and serve his community, including
17 but not limited to EducateNKY, the St. Elizabeth Healthcare Board of Trustees, the Ohio
18 National Mutual Holding Company, Inc. board of directors, the Northern Kentucky
19 Kindergarten Readiness Task Force, the Prichard Committee for Academic Excellence,
20 and LINK nky; and
21 WHEREAS, Dr. James Votruba led others with energy, vision, and an innate ability
22 to connect with others and make them feel the importance of their efforts and work; and
23 WHEREAS, Dr. James Votruba was considered a beacon, a mentor, and a role
24 model for many people across northern Kentucky and beyond; and
25 WHEREAS, Dr. James Votruba passed away on March 19, 2025, surrounded by
26 family; and
27 WHEREAS, Dr. James Votruba was preceded in death by his parents, Francis and
